headline: Combined Arms Continues to Combat Food Insecurity Among Veterans and Military Families
summary: Combined Arms remains steadfast in its mission to fight food insecurity among veterans, active duty service members, and their families, a challenge that continues to affect thousands across Southeast Texas and beyond. Since a significant spike in food assistance requests in 2021, Combined Arms has served more than 58,000 military-connected families through its food distribution efforts.
